China reiterated its commitment to "one country, two systems" for Taiwan, unveiling an anti-secession law.
Taiwan strongly opposes this move, fearing it legalizes invasion.
President Chen condemned Beijing's unilateral actions, warning of regional instability.
The US and EU also criticized China's legislation as counterproductive.
Taiwan plans to counteract the law through a referendum.
The Legislative Yuan will pass a resolution against Beijing's anti-secession efforts.
China clarified that the law aims to prevent Taiwan independence, not provoke conflict.
This law underscores China's stance against separatist activities, emphasizing peaceful reunification.
